            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2017-01-17 14:05:48" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>= a condition that affects the skin or surface, which probably covers diseases such as psoriasis, favus, leucoderma, but also mildew on cloth and walls; ► a person who suffers from this disease is considered ritually unclean, and therefore unable to participate in worship; clothes and buildings that are affected by it are unclean as well; ≈ regarded as infectious, and seen as a curse and a punishment from God</DefinitionShort>
